# Project/Underchex - Reference - Structure
Tags: #project #underchex #reference #structure #project-structure

## Overview
This document describes the Underchex repository structure.

## Directory Layout
- `spec/`: Language-agnostic game rules and test cases
  - `rules.md`: Game rules and piece movement patterns
  - `board.json`: Board definition (hexagonal grid with 6-way adjacency)
  - `pieces.json`: Piece definitions with movement patterns
  - `starting_position.json`: Initial board setup
  - `tests/move_validation.json`: Shared test cases for cross-impl validation
- `src/`: Implementation directories
  - `src/typescript/`: TypeScript + React web implementation (PRIMARY)
  - `src/web/`: Raw HTML + JS implementation (no deps)
  - `src/python/`: Python terminal CLI and tkinter GUI
  - `src/rust/`: Rust + WASM implementation
  - `src/kotlin/`: Kotlin/JVM CLI
  - `src/c/`: C + ncurses terminal implementation
  - `src/elixir/`: Elixir/OTP telnet server

## Conventions
- Each implementation is self-contained with its own build system
- All implementations must pass shared spec tests in `spec/tests/`
- AI engines are implemented per-implementation
- Cross-impl tests validate consistency across all implementations

